==English==

{{rank|Hart|social|shown|924|escape|Mr|shot|warm}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

# Facilitating or assisting in a specific act of [[#Noun|escape]].
# Helping to get around a limitation or regulation; as an [[escape sequence]], an [[escape clause]].
#*'''1988''', Kernighan and Ritchie, ''The C Programming Language'', Prentice Hall Software Series, ISBN 0-13-110370-9, 2nd edition page 37
#*:Certain characters can be represented in character and string contants by '''escape''' sequences like \n (newline); these sequences look like two characers, but represent only one.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The act of leaving a dangerous or unpleasant situation.
#: ''The prisoners made their escape by digging a tunnel''
# A key on most modern computer keyboards, sometimes abbreviated [[Esc]], and typically programmed to cancel some current operation.
# ''programming:'' The [[ASCII]] character represented by 27 (decimal) or 1B ([[hexadecimal]].)
#: ''You forgot to insert an '''escape''' in the datastream.''

